        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 23 at 11:16AM PDT by NWS Hanford CA</headline>
        <description>At 1115 AM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 13
miles west of Onion Valley Campground, or 21 miles west of
Independence, moving north at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Roaring River Ranger Station, Sentinel Campground, Canyon View
Campground, State Lakes, Monarch Ranger Station, Moraine Campground,
Cedar Grove, Sheep Creek Campground, and Mitchell Meadow.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
